inn1.comm: and he starts off with a wide, pitched wide outside the off stump and shaping away further, rightly called a wide
full and on the stumps, excellent delivery first-up, defended watchfully
another wide, again pitched wide outside the off stump and shaping away from the left-hander, Pathan struggling a bit to here
and again! another wayward delivery outside the off stump, out of reach and the umpire is not happy with the width - Pathan off to a dreadful start here!
off the mark with a bang! typical Gayle style! short and wide outside the off stump, Gayle leans back and cuts it away through point, powerful blow
no-ball! and the nightmare continues!
steered down to third man for an easy single
defended down on the off side
hit on the pad, appeal turned down, probably missing leg
Morton too off the mark in style! pitched up on the stumps and Morton drives it straight back down the track to the long-on fence, excellent timing and placement
excellent comeback delivery, Morton is once again hit on the pad, another huge appeal turned down, again probably missing leg - finally the the over comes to an end after 11 balls! what a start!
short of a good length delivery, defended to point
another good delivery from Patel, defended to midwicket, watchfully played
on the pads, turned away nicely to the fine leg region for a single
good length delivery, close to the off stump line, defended on the back-foot
good length delivery, pitched close to the off stump line, hint of away swing and Morton is beaten outside the off stump
short of a good length delivery, no swing there, coming in with the angle, defended on the back-foot
similar line and length, defended watchfully
short of a good length delivery, shaping away, Gayle goes back and drives it away towards mid-off, not a well timed shot and the ball came off the inner half of the bat
another good leave outside the off stump
good delivery, close to the off stump line and Gayle defends it down on the off side
defended awkwardly and the ball rolls down the track
maiden! good outswinger to end the over and Gayle leaves it through to the keeper
short and wide outside the off stump, cut away towards point, diving half-stop from Yuvraj there saves a certain boundary
hit on the pad, Gayle beaten for pace there, appeal for lbw turned down, missing leg by a long way
driven straight to Agarkar at mid-off

short of a good length delivery, excellent line and lenght, Gayle on the back-foot defending, ball clips the inside edge and rolls away behind the stumps, just missed the leg stump there, that was a close call!
good length delivery, driven well wide of the fielder at cover
defended on the back-foot, West Indies off to a good start here!
good length delivery on the middle and leg stump line, Morton stays back and clips it away through midwicket, the heavy outfield slows the ball down considerably and Harbhajan catches up
good length delivery, shaping away, Gayle gets forward and drives it away on the off side
cut away off the back-foot to the cover region, good looking shot but the placement was poor
pitched up on the stumps, in the slot and Gayle drives it away through mid-on, was spot-on with the placement on this occasion, top shot
left alone outside the off stump

short of a good length on the stumps, not pacey enough to trouble the batsman, Gayle rocks back and pulls it away to the midwicket fence, another good clean hit, another dreadful over from Pathan comes to an end.
driven away towards cover
turned away off the pads to deep square leg, easy two
called for overstepping, good length delivery and Morton drives it down to mid-on
short ball on the middle and leg stump line, awkward looking pull and the ball rolls down to fine leg

good length delivery, pitched in-line and drifting across, Gayle moves across a bit and glides it down to the third man fence, despairing dive from RP Singh in the deep ends in vain, excellent touch shot that
four more! slightly short and angling across, Gayle quickly gets into a good position and jabs it away to the wide long-on fence, West Indies off to a flyer here
starts off with a decent line and length delivery, defended back to the bowler
hint of inswing, defended on the fornt-foot but not cleanly
short and wide outside the off stump, cut away towards cover, again not timed well enough and the ball rolled away off the inner half of the bat

short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, Morton stands tall on the back-foot and drives it away through cover point for a brace, nicely opened the face of the bat at the point of impact to get the placement right
driven straight to the fielder at cover
defended on the back-foot and the ball rolls away towards point

good length delivery outside the off stump, Gayle rocks back and hammers it well over the fielder at mid-on, hit through the line and the ball just rocketed away up and over the fielder, that's a Gayle special!
driven wide of Agarkar at mid-off, quick single taken - excellent cricket
good length delivery, shaped away a touch and Morton is beaten outside the off stump
good length delivery, close to the off stump line and Morton drives it back to the bowler
short of a good length delivery, Morton drives off the back-foot, not a well timed shot and the ball flies away towards cover, falls just short of Kaif there and goes past him
good length delivery, driven down to mid-on, no room for a single there
wayward delivery down the leg side, extras continues to mount!
short of a good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, no width offered and Gayle tamely defends it back to the bowler
again slightly short and close to the off stump line, coming in with the angle, Gayle defends on the back-foot and the ball rolls away towards cover point
short and wide outside the off stump, horrible delivery to say the least! Gayle swats it away as if it was a fly, hammered through point and not a soul moved! Gayle on the rampage here!
four more! short of a good length delivery, close to the off stump line, Gayle comes down the track and swings hard, ball clips the top-edge and flies over the slip cordon
left alone outside the off stump

good length delivery and Gayle jabs it straight back down the track to the long-on fence, another powerful shot and this time he almost took out his partner at the other end - Gayle doing what he does best that's whipping the opposition witless, West Indies racing away at this stage
driven away on the off side
defended watchfully, ball rolls back to the bowler
good length delivery, again driven away towards cover
driven in the air, one bounce and straight to Agarkar at mid-on
short ball, a nothing delivery, Morton neatly pulls it away to the midwicket fence, Sehwag can do nothing but escort it to the fence!
driven wide of Harbhajn at mid-off, quick single taken - Harbhajan hits the stumps at the bowler's end but Morton was never in trouble, third umpire woken up, green light flashes
short ball, pitched in line and angling across, at this pace and with Gayle at the other end - forget it! pulled away in typical fashion to the midwicket fence, try stopping that!
down the leg side, close to a wide, Harbhajan gets away with it
defended on the front-foot
tossed up on the pads, defended to short midwicket
swept away nicely to fine leg for a brace
flighted delivery, turning in from wide outside the off stump, Morton quickly goes back and nudges it down to short third man for an easy single, well played
driven away through midwicket, easy single to end the over
full and on the stumps, bit of a surprise delivery, defended watchfully
good length delivery on the middle and leg stump line, turned away to deep square for a couple, played it late to get the placement right
on the middle and off stump line, driven straight to the fielder mid-off
Agarkar once again drifting onto middle and leg, Gayle shuffles across and turns it away through the vacant square leg region, two more added to the total
hit on the pad trying to flick
tossed on the off stump line, pushed to covers
similar delivery and again Lara lunges, bat ahead of the body but this time it takes the outside edge and it runs past the slip
drifting down the leg, Gayle tries to swing it away, doesn't connect properly and it rolls off the pads
pushed to the off side
swept for four and that's fifty for Gayle. 26 th half-century in the ODI format. It was tossed on the middle and leg, on a length, Gayle swept it off the length to the deep square leg fence
worked away to deep midwicket
On a length, slanting away, Gayle pushes his bat out, away from his body and the ball rolls to the off side
short of a lenght, pushed across, Gayle goes back and makes room by moving towards his leg stump and thrashes it to deep cover
off a short run-up, in the channel around off stump, pushed to covers

gone! Short of a length, pitched outside the off stump and it held its line, if anything, and Morton moves towards the ball and has a poke at it and ends up nicking it. So a wicket falls, against the run of play.
bouncer first up, and Sarwan sways away
driven to mid-off
floated outside the off stump, Gayle reaches out, and plays a square drive and it runs to left of the backward point where yuvraj dives to his left to make the stop
pitched on the off, turning in, tucked to Kaif, at midwicket
super doosra! faster and it pitched just outside the off stump and Sarwan shuffles across and pushes at it, playing for the turn and is beaten
on the legs, worked behind square leg
tossed up on the middle and off stump line, driven through extra cover to RP Singh
on a length, around the off stump and leaving the batsman, Gayle again is rooted at the crease and has a jab at it and it takes the inside edge and runs to shortish fine-leg
pushed to left of Yuvraj singh at cover
full, on the middle stump, Gayle drives it straight to mid-on

Hmm...! quite a funny-looking shot. Gayle goes down the track and finds the ball short for his lofted drive, so instead, waits, swivels and short-arm jabs it to deep midwicket. How he managed to do it, only he will know.
full-length delivery on the off and middle stump line, Sarwan comes forward and drives it back to the bowler. Good over from Agarkar. He varied his line and length to keep the batsman guessing.
driven to mid-off
outside the leg stump and turning in, Gayle goes for a drive, misses and harbhajan goes up in appeal. It clearly pitched outside the leg stump Bhaji!
pushed to point
gone! Sarwan goes sweeping. It pitched outside the off stump, on a length, and Sarwan went down on his knee and attempts a sweep shot but misses and the ball turns in and traps him in front.
tossed on the off and middle stump, Lara goes forward and pushes it to the on side
slower ball, on the leg and middle stump line, Gayle leans forward and dead bats it
thrashed through extra cover! Overpitched and Gayle indulges himself
adjusts his length, and on the off stump, pushed to point
on the legs, Gayle tries to whip it away, doesn't connect and it rolls down to the right of Dhoni
on a length but sliding down the legs, Gayle allows the ball to come to him and tickles it down to the fine-leg fence
right up to the bat and driven to mid-on
comes forward to play it quietly back down the pitch
slightly short, pitched outside the leg stump and spun sharply across the left hander and Lara goes back and works his wrists over time to turn the ball to the on side
driven to covers
tossed up on the off and middle stump line and it straightened after pitching, Lara  dances down the track and pushes it back
comes forward and pushes at a one that's turning away from him and the outside edge takes the ball to point
on a length, pushed across and Gayle shifts his weight back and punches it to Sehwag at short extra cover
similar delivery, played on the up to Sehwag again
full around the off stump, driven straight to Raina at mid-off and they take a quick run. Raina fails to gather the ball cleanly, it could have turned interesting if he had made a clean stop
back and across and pushes a good-length delivery to Kaif at covers
on the leg stump but Lara, as his wont, has shuffled outside the line of the ball and whips it to fine-leg for a single
outside the off stump, Gayle shifts his weight to his back foot and plays a horizontal cut past point.
beaten on the forward prod! tossed up on the leg and middle stump line, Lara lunges forward and pushes at it
worked away to midwicket and they take a run
back away to the leg side and pushes it back to harbhajan
reverse sweep for a four! tossed on the leg and middle stump and Gayle decides to go with the spin and hits it over point!
full and on the leg stump, Gayle pushes it to long-on
leg byes for four! Agarkar errs on line again, sliding down the leg, Gayle tries to whip it way, misses but it runs to fine-leg fence. The fine leg is up in the circle and so a poor delivery there
full and again on the legs, worked away to deep midwicket
on a length, slanting away, Lara comes forward and pushes it towards mid-off . Agarkar gets across to make the stop.
oh ho! that Lara whiplash drive is out! full and pushed across the left-hander but Lara pulls out his lovely cover drive but hits straight to covers.
Aha! that Lara pull! short of a length and on the middle and leg stump line, Lara goes back and across and takes his right foot off the ground and short-arm jabs it the midwicket fence
on the leg stump line, Gayle plays a forward defensive stroke
full and outside the leg stump and turning in a bit, Gayle tries to whip it through midwicket, doesn't connect and is rapped on the pads
comes forward and whips it to midwicket but finds Rahul Dravid, no chance of run
tossed up on the middle and off stump, full in length, driven hard to the right of Harbhajan who lunges to his side to make the stop
outside the leg stump, worked away to deep square leg where Agarkar fields
again on the leg stump and turning across the left-hand batsman, Lara lunges forward and tries to whip it across the line, gets a leading edge which goes in air towards the off side but no harm done.
Full and outside the off stump, pushed to back ward point
around the off stump line, full in length, and kept a bit low, pushed to Kaif at covers
driven out to sweeper cover
on a length, just outside the off stump, Lara moves towards the ball and offers the full face of the blade in defence
turned down the fine-leg for a single
glided to third man for a single
worked through the covers
beaten outside the off stump
strays down the legside this time, and is rightly called wide by the Umpire
full delivery from Pathan, down the legside, Lara tries to work it down to fineleg, gets a tickle on it, its neatly collected by Dhoni behind the stumps
good length delivery on the pads, its worked away to deep squareleg for a single
change of pace from Pathan, Gayle picks the slower one and works it away to deep mid wicket for a single
short of a length from Pathan, Lara, standing on one leg, with his right foot in the air, pulls it away to squareleg for one
full delivery from Pathan to wind up the over, down the leg side again, would have been a certain wide had Lara not got a tickle on it, neat take by Dhoni moving down to his right side
short of a length and coming in towards the hips, tucked to midwicket
short of a length, around the off stump, pushed to covers
on a length, angling down the leg, turned away behind square leg
full and on the middle and off stump line. Lara goes back and across and whips it  to midwicket
full and on the leg and middle again, Lara goes back and across, ending up outside the line of the ball and tucks it away to fine-leg
on a length, angling in towards the off stump, Lara hops back and pushes it to the on side
gone! on a length, pushed across Lara who leans forward and drives it on the up to left of Kaif, at covers, who dives low to his left to catch it. Very good catch
outside the off stump, left alone
pitched outside the off stump and shaping away, Chanderpaul leans forward towards the ball and at the last minute shoulders arms
short of length, pushed across Chanderpaul who comes forward and pushes it to Yuvraj at point
tucked away to fine-leg
hits the deck hard, short of a length outside the off stump and angling in. Chanderpaul goes back and pushes it to covers
full and on the leg and middle, worked through midwicket for a single
on a length, pitched on the middle stump and going towards the leg and Gayle is cramped for room as he tries to whip it away but doesn't connect
nudged past point for a single
short of length and directed towards the off stump, Chanderpaul stands tall and pushes it straight to cover
On a length around the off stump, Gayle moves back and pushes it to Kaif at covers
cut to the right of third man and Sehwag lets rip a good throw but Gayle makes to the crease in time and he is just three runs short of a century
pushed to covers
on a length, around the off stump and Gayle goes back and punches it to mid-off
full and angled across, left alone
full around the off stump, Gayle comes forward and drives it to Raina at mid-off and raina has a shy at the non-strikers' end as Chanderpaul had backed up a  bit.
on a length and kicking up, Gayle goes back to punch it to the off side
short and rising, Gayle shuffles across, gets outside the line and tucks it behind square-leg. Just one run short of the magic mark now!
driven through sweeper cover
full and sliding down leg, Chanderpaul gets across and whips it past square-leg and by the time the deepmidwicket fielder gets across to his left, they run two
beaten! tries to cut a ball, just outside the off stump but is cramped for room. Too close to cut
good length delivery outside the off stump, forced away off the back-foot to the point region, crowd waits in anticipation
another decent delivery outside the off stump off stump, no shot offered, Gayle bit watchful here with just one run away from what will be a fantastic century.
defended outside the off stump
good length delivery, close to the off stump line, defended on the back-foot
there it is! good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Gayle pushes forward and the ball rolls away off the inside edge to the square leg region, easy single brings up the magic figure
pitched up and angling across, Chanderpaul drives away from his body, ball clips the outside edge and races away to the third man fence
cut away straight to the fielder at point

and just when you think you have seen it all Gayle hits a one-handed six over midwicket! fraction short and outside the off stump, Gayle on the back-foot pulling,  took his bottom hand off the bat as he played that shot but the ball flew away over the midwicket fence - awesome shot
another short ball and this time Gayle pulls it away wide of the fielder at short fine leg, played it late to get the placement right
driven wide of the fielder at mid-on
good length delivery outside the off stump, defended to point
fuller length delivery, bit wide outside the off stump, Chanderpaul reaches out for it and drives it wide of the fielder at cover, easy single to end the over
wayward delivery outside the off stump, rightly called a wide
driven straight to the fielder at point
good length delivery outside the off stump, hint of away swing, Chanderpaul gets well forward and drives it away to deep cover for a single

good length delivery outside the off stump, Gayle moves forward and across and has a mighty swing, ball clips the inside edge and rockets away to the fine leg fence, as they say - 'fortune favours the brave'!
slower delivery on the stumps, Gayle spots it early and plays it away towards cover
awkwardly played back to the bowler
fulltoss outside the off stump, Gayle makes room and that takes him away from the line, in the end drives it wide of the fielder at cover for a single
fraction short and turning across, Gayle leans back and cuts it away towards deep point for an easy single
turning in from outside the leg stump, worked away off the back-foot to square leg

take that! fuller length delivery outside the off stump, in the slot, Gayle just gets his front-foot out of the way and murders it straight back past the bowler to the long-off fence, Gayle continues on his merry way, another powerful boundary added to the total
defended away towards point
turned away well wide of the fielder at midwicket
tossed up and turning across, Gayle comes down the track and strokes it away to long-on, there is protection in the deep and he gets just a single for that
yorker first-up, defended back to the bowler
good length delivery, Gayle leans back and drives it away behind point
another line and length delivery from Agarkar, Chanderpaul had no option but to defend it back to the bowler - excellent over so far
nudged away well wide of the fielder at mid-off

got'm! good length delivery on the pads, Gayle turns it away in the air to the midwicket region, Dravid fielding at the edge of the dives across to his left and takes it cleanly, bit of a soft dismissal and an anti-climax, Agarkar rewarded from some excellent seam bowling
Agarkar probes Samuels outside off first up, Samuels has a good look at it and lets it through to the wicketkeeper
pitches one outside leg and turninng across Chanderpaul, Chanderpaul plays it away wide of Dravid at midiwcket and takes off for a single
flatter deklivery, on the middle and let stump, Samuels moves his frontfoot outside the line of the offstump and works it away past Kaif at midwicket for a single
outside the legstump again, worked away to Dravid at short midwicket
driven to Kaif at short cover
outside the legstump again, and Chanderpaul works it away backward of square, engouth time for a single there
Harbhajan Singh ends his over with a full toss, its neatly driven down the ground, to longon for a single
good delivery by Agarkar, full and right up in the block hole, its driven down to long-off for one

full delivery again, this time Chanderpaul cheekily flicks it away to fineleg, its a brilliant dive by Raina who is fielding at short fineleg, dives to his left and saves a certain boundary, keeps it down to a single
another yorker from Agarkar, this time Samuels cant do much, ends up playing it straight back to the bowler
another fuller length delivery follows, and this time Samuels drives it down to longon and takes a single before the fielder can come in, field the ball and return it back to the bowler
driven to Munaf Patel, who is positioned at the edge of the circle at mid-off, Chanderpaul takes a quick csingle
driven down to Munaf Patel who has moved back to longon this time, just a single
starts off with a 69 mph delivery on the leg stump, Samuels plays it back to the onside, Pathan quick to move from his follow through and field the ball
slower delivery yet again, Samuels tries to make room and play it to the offside, misses the ball and is rapped on the pads, the ball rolls away to the off-side, and the batsmen steal a single
change of pace, but losing direction this time, wide outside the off stump, its rightly called wide by Umpire Rauf, Chanderpaul goes after it but can't make contact

what a catch!! athleticism at its best! that was a good length delivery from Pathan, Chanderpaul has a swing at it, doesn't keep the ball down, the ball dies as it reaches Sehwag who is positioned on the fence, but he makes good ground, and times his dive forward to perfection, pouches the ball neatly and comes up with the ball
cut away backward of point for a single
fuller length delivery on the stumps, Baugh drives it back to Pathan
cut away to deep thirdman for a single, will keep strike at the start of the next over
quicker one from Agarkar, at 83mph, Baugh opens the face of the bat and runs it down to Yuvraj at point
good looking stroke from Baugh, its fuller in length from Agarkar, Baugh drives it uppishly throgh covers, and takes a run, there;s Kaif sweeping the cover fence there
driven to long-on for a singpe, Munaf Patel the man there
cut away to the right of Yuvraj Singh at point, moves quickly, but can;t prevent a single
again cut away to deep cover for one, Mohammad Kaif the man there
the last ball of Agarkar's spell, its full and its neatly driven down to long-on

mighty heave this one!! its short from PAthan, just at the right place for Baugh to heave across the line, he swings across, gets it off the middle of the bat, and the ball sails high and wide over the mid-wicket fence
opens the face of the bat and runs it down to Raina at deep thirdman

driven down to long-off, take the first run quickly and think about the second, Samuels takes off for the second run, but Baugh is not too impressed, holds his ground at the striker's end, the fielder at long-off fires in a perfect throw back to Pathan who is up at the stumps, and Pathan duly whips off the bails, its bye-bye for Samuels
single taken this time
good length delivery from Pathan, Bravo tries to work it to the legside, ball comes off the pad and rolls away to the offside, scramble through for a legbye

good length delivery from Pathan, Baugh steps outside the offstump and tries to sweep it down fine to the legside, misses the line of the ball and is hit on the body, even as the ball rolls away on the off-side, the two batsmen scamper through for a run - thats a legbye to end the inning

inn2.comm: bang on target first up. Short of a length, on the off stump, Sehwag hops back and pushes it to the on side
bouncer that sails well over Sehwag. This one was wasted but I am sure Windies will try to pin Sehwag with few short pitched stuff
full on the off and middle stump line, Sehwag whips it across the line to square leg
pushed to point
short of length, drifting towards the pads, Sehwag tries to work it to the on side, doesn't make contact and the ball rolls off the pads to shortish fine-leg
full outside the off stump and shaping away ever so slightly, Sehwag guides it past gully and beats the thirdman fielder.
full and outside off again but this one holds its line, Sehwag gets across and shoulders his arms
ooh! full outside the off stump, and angling away, Sehwag has a flash at it and it goes in the air, but to the left of point
good-length delvery outside the off stump, Dravid gets across and you guessed right, lets it go.
full and driven to mid-off and they take a quick single
on a length, and angling towards the hips, Dravid tries to work it to on side, fails and is rapped on the pads
hurled outside the off stump, Dravid lunges forward, upto the pitch of the ball, covers his off stump and lets it go to the keeper
just short of a length, on the off and middle stump line but Dravid hops across, uses his wrists overtime and whips it across towards midwicket

OMG! almost a catch! short of a length and shaping towards the hips, Sehwag gets inside the line and tries to whip it the onside but gets a edge onto the thighpads and it goes up in the air. Fidel Edwards makes a valiant effort to reach the ball but ...

oh! almost a run-out now! Sehwag cuts to right of point and sets off but Dravid is not, rightly, interested and if the throw had found its mark, Sehwag would have been short of the crease. The two batsmen get together for a chat
short of length, on the hips, Sehwag tries to whip it, doesn't connect, and the ball rolls, off the pads, to the fine-leg fence
bouncer and Dravid goes for a pull but is beaten by the bounce and pace
superbly played hook shot! Short and rising, Dravid gets inside the line and hooks in front of squareleg and keeps it down as well. Fab shot!
Ah! now a beautiful off drive! Full and on the off stump line, Dravid leans forward, and caresses it past the bowler
cut ferociously but straight to covers.
short of length, on the leg and middle stump line, whipped to deep midwicket
similar delivery , turned to midwicket where Sarwan makes the stop
just short of a length and again on the leg and middle stump, Dravid works it to right of Samuels at midwicket
short of a length, around the off stump, and Sehwag hops and pushes it back to the bowler
Arrgh! wide outside the off stump. It must have slipped out of his hands.
short of length and again on the leg and middle stump, Sehwag rocks back, gets his left foot off the ground, whips it straight to Samuels at square-leg
action replay there! again whipped to Samuels
another wide outside the off stump. With the round-arm action of Edwards, it will happen now and then as the right arm falls a bit too much away at release
bouncer and swayed away
another wide outside the off stump. Lara runs acros to Edwards, has a short chat,  and goes back to his position at covers
sliding down the legs, tucked to deep fine-leg.  Eight extras already from West Indies.
on the legs, whipped through the midwicket gap and they run two. Sehwag seems to be limping a bit.  Don't know whats the problem. Hope that's not serious.
ooh! full and outside the off stump and Sehwag throws his hands at it,  it goes in the air, just  to the left of backward point.
tip and run! run with the stroke. Dravid dead-batted it close to the stumps on the of side and Sehwag calls for a quick run and off they go.
short of a length and well outside the off stump. Sehwag gets back and across and has a lazy waft at it, doesn't connect.
fuller and in the channel outside the off stump, Sehwag moves in line, pushes it to right of cover and they run hard for two
slower ball, on the legs, Sehwag gets inside the line and whips it , in the air, through the midwicket gap. Nice pick up shot.
full-length delivery, just outside the off stump, Dravid digs it out and pushes it to mid-off
short of a length, on the off stump, Dravid goes back and then moves his left foot across towards the ball and offers the dead bat in defence
short of length, on the off stump, Dravid goes back and across, and whips it to midwicket.

Outrageous! six over the keeper's head! short and rising, just outside the off stump and Dravid goes for a pull and the top edge sends the ball screaming up and over for a six! Very short boundaries here.
low full-toss, pushed to mid-off
on a length, just outside the off stump, Dravid goes back and across and punches it to Morton, at extra cover
on a length, pushed across Sehwag, who comes forward and pushes it ,with a closed face of the bat, back to bowler
short of a length, on the legs, Sehwag tries to work it away on the on side but misses and the ball rebounds of the thigh pad and  rolls back down the track
now a wide down the leg side. Full and drifting down leg, Sehwag tries to play a pick-up shot, doesn't connect
arrgh! now a no-ball. West Indies are playing perfect hosts here. 11 extras already, 4 wides and 2 no-balls
flashed through covers for four! hit on the up. It was a length ball, pushed across Sehwag who comes forward and the drives it on the up
short of length, angling away, Sehwag goes back, opens the face of his bat and runs it to the thirdman
full, driven to mid-on
slanted across, outside the off stump, Dravid lunges forward, covers the line and lets it go
full-length delivery on the legs, pushed to midwicket. Finally the misery ends for Bradshaw: its the end of the over!
full and outside the off stump, Sehwag comes forward and drives it in the air to the left of the bowler who stuck his left hand out but the ball brushes his fingers on  its way to mid-off
on the legs, turned away to long leg
short of length, coming in from outside the off stump, Dravid gets inside the line and whips it to midwicket
short of length, and angling towards Dravid's hips, tucked away to long-leg
on a length, around the off stump, Sehwag gets across, steers it to Lara at cover
full and on the middle and leg stump line, Dravid comes forward and pushes it ,across the pads, back to the bowler
on a length, angled across, Dravid gets behind the line and punches it back down the pitch
fuller this time, just outside the off stump and Dravid is quick to get onto his front foot and drives straight to Chanderpaul at mid-off
gentle stuff outside the off, Dravid bends his right knee, and late-cuts it to thirdm an

Gone! got his man! bit bizaare actually! First Sehwag goes for a wild heave over the bowler but only manages to send the ball in a orbit up over mid-off, where Marlon samuels misjudges it as he goes back and doesn't get a hand on it. But here is where the Indians helped. They turn for the second run, rather Dravid comes back without any hesitation but Sehwag, who is caught ball watching, is late to get off  and fails to reach the crease in time. Samuels had fired the throw straight to the keeper who took off the bails in a flash. It should have been a comfortable two, if Sehwag had not been ball watching.
short and Dravid pulls it imperiously through the midwicket
full and outside the off stump, Dravid lunges forward and lets it go
on a length, around the middle stump, Dravid goes back and tucks it close on the on side and they take a single
full and pushed across the left-handed Pathan who punches it to mid-on
full and slanting away, Pathan drives a bit early and gets a leading edge through gully to thirdman

Pathan departs! short of a good length and bit wide outside the off stump, a relatively innocuous delivery, Pathan has a wild slash at it with no real footwork - thick edge and Morton at second slip sallows it cleanly, Bradshaw gets one to his name - India two down.
way outside the off stump
good length delivery, defended watchfully
bit wide outside the off stump, no shot offered
another line and length delivery, defended back to the bowler
on the middle and leg stump line, turned away through square leg for a brace
again defended back to the bowler
good length delivery outside the off stump, hint of away swing, Draivd is drawn forward into the drive, ball clips the edge and rolls down to third man
short of a good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Yuvraj stands tall on the back-foot and punches it away towards midwicket, no room for a single there
good length delivery on the pads, Yuvraj shuffles across bit, gets well inside the line and nicely turns it away behind square on the leg side, easy two
good length delivery, angling across, Yuvraj stretches well forward and drives it away through the gap between mid-off and cover
drifting down the leg side, Dravid looking to flick it away fine fails to make contact, ball clips the pad and rolls down to fine leg
short of a good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, good tight delivery to end the over, Yuvraj on the back-foot defending.

slower delivery on the middle and leg stump line, Dravid looking to whip it away through midwicket is beaten by the lack of pace, ball clips the leading edge and rolls away towards cover point, that could have gone anywhere!
good length delivery, angling across the right-hander, Dravid pushes forward and forces it away towards mid-off, watchfully played
good length delivery, Dravid stays back and dabs it down to short third man

good length delivery, slanting across but close to the off stump line, Dravid stays back and steers it down to third man for an easy single, waited for the ball and nicely opened the face of the bat at the last moment to get the placement right
good length delivery outside the off stump, driven straight to the fielder at mid-off
and again, another no-nonsense delivery from Bradshaw, Yuvraj stands tall on the back-foot and drives it down to mid-off

pitched up and angling in, Dravid leans forward to the pitch of the delivery and drives it straight back down the track to the long-off fence, perfect foot-work, head over the ball and the bat coming down straight - lovely shot
nudged down to third man for an easy single, this is good cricket from the India captain
left alone outside the off stump

four more! good length delivery outside the off stump, possibly moving away a touch, Yuvraj pushes forward into the off-drive, ball clips the outside edge and races away well wide of the lone slip fielder, would have been an easy chance if a second silip was in place
steered down to third man
turned away straight to the fielder at square leg
defended down on the off side
good length delivery outside the off stump, Yuvraj on the front-foot driving, ball zips past the outside edge
another tight delivery, close to the off stump line and Yuvraj watchfully defends it away towards cover
cut away off the back-foot to the point region, not a well timed shot
driven wide of the fielder at point, excellent dive from Bravo there saves runs, this is turning out to be a good over for West Indies

maiden! good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Yuvraj drives off the back-foot, ball clips the inner half of the bat and rolls down to mid-on, after that expensive over from Taylor, Bradshaw pulls it back a bit for West Indies.
good length delivery, Dravid on the front-foot driving, ball takes the outside edge and races away towards third man, good delivery first-up from Bravo
on the middle and leg stump line, turned away towards midwicket
way outside the off stump
good length delivery, driven straight to the fielder at mid-off
driven straight to the fielder at cover

bit of width offered outside the off stump and Yuvraj cuts it away well wide of the fielder at backward point, Bradshaw hurtles across from third man, swoops low down and flicks the ball in from right in front of the ropes - excellent effort
defended back to the bowler
slower delivery on the middle and leg stump line, Dravid clips it away in the air to the deep midwicket region
defended on the front-foot
another good delivery, defended watchfully

Bradshaw strikes again and this time it's the slower delivery that gets him a wicket! on the middle and off stump line, Yuvraj looking to loft it over the fielder at mid-on fails to connect properly, ball spoons up towards mid-on, Samuels there back-tracks, keeps his eye on the ball and at the last moment dives full length and takes it with both hands, amazing catch!
drifting down the leg side, easy picking, Dravid gets well inside the line and flicks it down to fine leg, excellent touch shot to break the ice.
defended on the front-foot
played away towards short midwicket
way outside the off stump, wasted delivery
another extra! this time it way down the leg side
good length delivery, much better line and length, defended watchcully
left alone outside the off stump
not again! another one down the leg side, Bravo clearly struggling here
on the middle and leg stump line, turned away towards square leg
good length delivery, edged away towards third man
defended towards cover, Bradshaw continues to impress
another line and lenght delivery, angling across, Kaif leaves it through to the keeper
forced away towards cover point
good length delivery on the stumps, driven straight to the fielder at cover
short of a good length delivery, angling across, Kaif stands tall on the back-foot and drives it away through the gap between the cover fielders
good length delivery, close to the off stump line, Dravid gets well forward and drives it away straight to the fielder at cover
pitched up on the middle and leg stump line, turned away straight to the fielder at midwicket, timing was good but the placement was poor
good length delivery, angling in from outside the off stump, Dravid gets into a good position and drives it away well wide of the fielder at mid-on
another easy single, good looking square-drive and the ball races away through cover point
close to the off stump line, eased away on the off side
good length delivery on the stumps, Dravid drives it straioght back past the bowler to the long-on region
Full and on the leg and middle, worked through the midwicket gap
on a length, just outside the off stump, pushed past point for a single
full and wide outside the off stump, slapped to deep cover. Dravid came forward, reached for the wide one and square-drove it off the front foot
good-length delivery, just on the off stump, pushed to point
dropped! at covers. Short of length, well outside the off stump and Kaif thumped it, off the front foot and Lara dives to his left, got a hand to it but couldn't quite hang onto it.
tossed on the middle stump line, Dravid comes forward and turns it behind squareleg
on the leg and middle stump line, tucked away to short fine-leg
slower, on the middle stump, Dravid comes forward and whips it through midwicket
slightly short, outside the off stump, Kaif waits on his front foot and taps it past point
appeal for lbw as Dravid goes for a sweep from outside the off stump and is rapped just outside the line and it rolls toward short fine-leg
short and well outside the off stump, Dravid waits and cuts it past the point to bring up his fifty!
short and rising on the off and middle , Kaif pulls, off the front foot, to deepmidwicket
half-volley outside the off stump, Kaif comes forward to drive it through the covers
slower ball but loses control over line and it slips down the leg side
short of length, around the off stump, Dravid bends his right knee slightly and taps it down to thirdman
short of a length, on the off and middle stump line, tucked to Sarwan at square-leg

full and shaping towards the middle stump, Kaif goes for a drive but the inside edges onto his front pad and it rolls back to the bowler. The left foot was kept bit too across and he had to end up playing around it and hence the not so flash result
tapped to right of Sarwan at point
short of length, on the middle stump, pushed out to the right of mid-on
slower and tossed on the off stump, short of length. Dravid comes forward, waits and bends his right knee while executing a delectable late cut
quicker one, outside the off stump and Kaif gets beaten as he shapes to cut
driven to mid-on

full and on the off stump line, driven straight back down the pitch, and the ball crashes into the stumps on the non-striker's ends and runs to
short of length, cut behind point
on a length,o utside the off stump, punched through covers
overpitched on the off and middle, driven imperiously past the bowler and they run hard for two with Kaif reaching his crease just in time
driven back down the pitch, in the air, just falls short of a diving Fidel
tucked to the midwicket
flatter and outside the off stump, Kaif cuts it fine to the thirdman fence
tossed on the middle, driven back down the pitch
slightly short, just outside the off stump, punched to deep cover
driven back to the bowler
tossed up on the off stump, driven to long-on
full and on the leg and middle stump line, Kaif tries to whip it to the on side, gets a leading edge and the ball rolls to mid-off
full and on the legs, turned straight to Sarwan at midwicket
if not for the no-ball, it would have been a wide. A attempted yorker which ends up as a low full toss down the leg side, Kaif fails to get a touch
pushed back down the pitch, Bravo gets across to make the stop
pushed just short of Lara, at covers, and they go through for a quick run
oh ho! slower ball, full in length, Dravid spotted it early, waited and lofted it over wide mid-on for a lovely four
driven past the bowler for a single
on the middle stump, Dravid goes back and plays it to the off side
driven to Lara at short midwicket
beaten on the forward prod, ball rolls to the off side off the pads
driven to mid-on
tossed up on the of stump, pushed to right of cover
cut straight to the short third man
tossed on the off stump, driven to long-on
much slower, outside the off stump, Dravid tries to whip it across but doesnt time it properly
turned to the onside
on the legs, turned to short fine-leg, Dravid wants a run but Kaif is not interested
comes forward to a full-length delivery and drives to long-on
bang! good delivery on the stumps and Dravid dispatches it over the wide long-on fence, excellent hit through the line. going down on one knee as he played the shot
cut away off the back-foot to the point region
on the pads, turned away towards short fine leg, no room for a singlea
again turned away towards short fine leg
driven away through cover point, easy single to end the over
defended outside the off stump
driven off the back-foot, ball rolls back to the bowler
fraction short, punched off the back-foot and the ball races away through cover point
another right delivery from Gayle, Dravid ends up defending back to the bowler
flat delivery on the middle and off stump line, Dravid swings across the line and gets it away to deep midwicket

too straight a delivery, turned away behind square on the leg side, Kaif takes on the fielder coming in from the deep and makes it back safely for the second - phew! another quick over from Gayle comes to an end
turning in from outside the off stump, driven off the back-foot and gets it through the gap between point and cover
fraction short, Dravid quickly picks up the length, rocks back and pulls it away to the backward square leg fence, that's a much needed boundary for India
quicker delivery outside the off stump, Dravid stays back and taps it down to short third man for a single
turned away off the pads and the ball goes wide of the fielder at short third man
turned away off the pads and the ball goes wide of the fielder at short third man
forced away towards point
cracking drive! tossed up delivery outside the off stump, in the slot and Dravid drills it through covers
forced away on the off stump
flat delivery, lofted over midwicket for a single
driven down to long-on
on the middle and leg stump line, Kaif comes down the track and lofts it neatly over the fielder at midwicket
turned away to deep square leg, good over for India comes to an end - 10 runs coming off it.

DROPPED! short ball and Kaif pulls it away towards deep square leg, Edwards there in the deep moves across nicely, gets right under the ball - after doing all the hard work he then drops a sitter - what a left-off!
cut away straight to the fielder at point, powerful shot but the placement was poor
edged away towards third man, easy single
driven away towards point
turned away on the leg side
good length delivery, angling across, driven down to long-off for a single
starts off with a horrible delivery, full and on the pad and Dravid clips it through midwicket, flick of the wrists and the ball sped away off the middle of the bat

good length delivery but again on the middle and leg stump line, Dravid leans well forward and drives it away through the gap between mid-on and midwicket, one of the hardest shots in the book but Dravid made it look easy
on the middle and off stump line, much better delivery from Edwards, Dravid is made to defend
pitched up and angling in, Dravid pushes forward and drives it down to long-on, just a single on this occasion

good length delivery, cutting in from outside the off stump, Kaif stands tall on the back-foot and punches it straight back past the bowler to the long-off region, Edwards on his followthrough battled hard to get a touch on it but ...
good length delivery outside the off stump, driven down to long-off for an easy single, Dravid moves to 95 with that single and he will retain the strike, end of a good over for India
drive straight to the cover fielder who is at the edge of the cricle, early call and a quick single taken
pitched up on the stumps, driven just wide of the fielder at mid-on
defended down on the leg side and Kaif takes off for the single, Bravo moves across quickly but fails to cut off the single
neatly driven down to long-on, again just a single
pitched up on the middle and off stump line, Dravid makes room and hammers it straight back down the ground to the long-on region

fulltoss on the pads, possibly the yorker gone wrong, Kaif tucks it away behind square leg for just a single, was there to be hit but Kaif was taken by surprise and in the end it was more of a defensive flick than a full-blooded shot
good length delivery outside the off stump, slanting in, Kaif gets forward and drives it in the air and past Lara at covers
short of a good length delivery, cutting in from outside the off stump, Dravid stands tall on the back-foot and dabs it behind point for an easy single that takes him to 99!
fulltoss on the pads and once again Kaif misses out, turned away behind square for just a single
there it is! good length delivery on the middle and leg stump line, Dravid gets well forward and drives it down to long-on for an easy single
again driven down to long-on
edged and through! good length delivery outside the off stump, Dravid on the back-foot driving, ball clips the outside edge and races away to the third vacant man fence
driven away through midwicket, easy two and now it's almost down to run a ball!
good length delivery outside the off stump, driven away to sweeper cover for a single, that all what they need
turned away straight to the fielder at short fine leg, quick single taken
good length delivery, driven well wide of the fielder at cover
crucial blow! good length delivery on the stumps, excellent change of pace from Bravo and Dravid ends up hitting it high up towards long-on, Taylor there in the deep judges it to perfection.
wicket to wicket delivery, driven back to the bowler, end of a successful over from Bravo
good length delivery, pitched in line and angling across, Dhoni stands his ground and cuts hard, ball zips past the outside edge
good length delivery, similar line and lenght and this time Dhoni drives it down to mid-off, diving stop saves runs but fails to cut off the single
turned away towards midwicket, misfield from Sarwan and the batsmen steal a single
defended down on the leg side, poor delivery
MAX! good length delivery, pitched in line and angling across, Dhoni steps forward and lofts it straight down the ground and the ball sails over the long-off fence, good clean hit
fraction short and angling across, Dhoni comes down hard on it and the ball rockets away to the third man fence, diving effort in the deep ends in vain - this is Dhoni at his best!
driven wide of the cover fielder and the single will keep him on strike
full and driven powerfully to long-off
yorker length, on the middle stump line, dug out, back to the bowler
fifty up for Kaif! driven to long-off. And Kaif finds some runs, after a long drought.
low full-toss, on the legs, swatted away to long leg. Dhoni would be ruing a chance to hit a four
overpitched outside the off stump, Kaif comes forward and drives it long-off
beaten outside the off stump! short of a length, outside the off stump that helds its line and Kaif pokes at it, misses
on a length, around the off stump, square driven to point. Two dots balls in a row!
another dot ball! full and on the leg and middle stump line, turned straight to midwicket!
pressure tells on Kaif! He moves away from his leg stump and has a go at a length-delivery on the stumps but drags it down to midwicket
Game on! swatted straight to .... you guessed it right .... midwicket!
Ah! just a run. full and angling intowards the pads, Kaif has a flash, misses and it runs to short third man for a run
a mis-field results in a run! full toss and driven straight to Sarwan at point, who fumbles. Dhoni on strike now! Here we go!
Yes Sir! a four! Attempted yorker turned into a low full toss. Dhoni gets his left foot out of the line, outside the leg stump and thumps it to deep midwicket

gone! Game on folks! Full-length delivery on the middle stump, Dhoni again takes his left foot just outside the line and whacks it towards long-on. It flew straight to the fielder there. Don't go anywhere!

oh! almost a chance! Kaif has a go at a full length delivery outside the off stump and the outside edge sends the ball flying to the right of a diving Baugh. That four changes it all - just 14 required now from 13 balls
oh! Lucky Kaif! has a almighty heave to a full-length delivery, outside the off stump but it falls between the long-on fielder running in and Lara who runs from covers
edge and a four! slash outside the off stump and it flies to the third man fence, Just 8 runs now,
pushed across, yorker length and Raina tries to run it down to third man, misses
short of length, around the off stump, pushed to cover, where Lara fields and has a shy at non-strikers end and if he had hit Kaif would have been dead
on a length, outside the off stump, driven to long-off. 7 off 8
on the pads, turned past midwicket for a comfortable couple of runs. Only 5 more needed for India now
yorker length, on the leg stump, dug out to long on. So just four runs needed now.  should be easy for India but ...
yorker length on the off stump, driven to cover
Tension mounts now! Kaif hits straight to Lara at covers again! what drama here!
short of length, on the stumps, swatted away to deep midwicket. Raina on the strike now. Here we go!

almost a runout! drives straight to Lara at midwicket who hurls it to the non-strikers' end but Bravo doesn't attempt to take the throw, thinks it will hit the stump straight, it doesn't and they miss a runout
That's it! game over! Kaif slams a full-length delivery, just outside the off stump, through the covers and finds the fence! India register their 17th successful run chase on the trot.
